## Promotion Picker — Full Implementation Plan (rev 3)

### Overview
When a pawn reaches the last rank, intercept the move before committing it, show a board-anchored square picker (Option A), then apply the move with the chosen piece.

Findings addressed:
- (High) Stale-move guard: picker commit revalidates live-play preconditions; all lifecycle exit paths clear pendingPromotion
- (Medium) Resign path: setPendingPromotion(null) added to handleResign alongside setResolvedReview(null)
- (Medium) Tests: squareToPercent test case corrected (e8/black-orientation → top: 87.5, not 100)
- (Low) Aftermath: handlePromotionPick routes through applyPlayerMoveAndAdvance — no third copy of the branch
- (Open) Cancel clears selection fully via clearMoveHighlights; re-clicking the pawn is trivial

---

## Data Flow

```
Player drags or clicks pawn to promotion square
  → handleDropPiece / handleSquareClick  (ChessGame.tsx)
    → applyPlayerMove(from, to) / handleDrop(from, to)  (controller)
      → isPromotionNeeded() true, no promotion arg
        → returns { applied: false, requiresPromotion: true }
    → ChessGame: setPendingPromotion({ from, to })
    → handleDropPiece returns false  (piece snaps back)
    → handleSquareClick: return early without clearing selection

PromotionPicker overlay renders over board
  → user clicks piece
    → handlePromotionPick(piece)
      1. revalidate: isGameActive && isViewingLive && chess.turn() === correct side
         if invalid → setPendingPromotion(null), return
      2. setPendingPromotion(null)
      3. applyPlayerMoveAndAdvance(from, to, piece)  [shared aftermath]
  → user clicks backdrop
    → handlePromotionCancel()
      → setPendingPromotion(null)
      → clearMoveHighlights()  [fully clears any selected pawn + move dots]

Any lifecycle exit (revert / resign / new game / reset / navigation)
  → setPendingPromotion(null) called in each exit path
```

---

