# Plan: Pass/Fail Overlay on Review Position Warning Box

## Context

When a ghost opponent targets a past blunder, a "Review Position" warning toast appears in the info panel. Currently, this toast vanishes the instant the user makes their move. The pass/fail result only arrives 1-3 seconds later when analysis completes. No visual feedback appears on the warning box itself.

**Goal**: Keep the warning box visible after the user moves, overlay a large green checkmark (pass) or red X (fail) when analysis returns, keep it visible until the user's next move, and support stacking with a new active review.

---

## Type

In `src/components/chess-game/types.ts`:

```typescript
export type ResolvedReview = {
  moveIndex: number;         // identity — ties overlay to a specific review move
  result: 'pending' | 'pass' | 'fail';
};
```

The `moveIndex` field solves late-analysis resurrection: when `AnalysisEffects` resolves an old review, it checks `resolvedReview.moveIndex` matches before updating. If the overlay was already cleared (null) or belongs to a different review, the late result is ignored (backend submission still proceeds regardless).

---

## Synchronous Pending Transition (no flicker)

The previous plan used a `useEffect` to detect `isReviewMomentActive` going false, but that fires _after_ paint — producing one frame with neither the active toast nor the pending replacement.

**Fix**: Set `resolvedReview` to pending **synchronously inside `applyPlayerMove`** in `src/hooks/useChessGameController.ts:162`, right where `blunderReviewId` is already captured and nulled. This is the shared path for both click-to-move and drag/drop.

```typescript
// useChessGameController.ts, inside applyPlayerMove, line ~162
if (blunderReviewId !== null) {
  pendingSrsReviewRef.current = {
    blunderId: blunderReviewId,
    moveIndex: committed.moveIndex,
    userMoveSan: committed.moveSan,
    srs: blunderReviewSrs,
  };
  setBlunderReviewId(null);
  setBlunderReviewSrs(null);
  setResolvedReview({ moveIndex: committed.moveIndex, result: 'pending' }); // NEW
}
```

On the same render: `isReviewMomentActive` goes false (active toast unmounts), `resolvedReview` goes non-null (pending toast mounts). No gap.

---

## Clearing `resolvedReview` — All Paths

### On next successful player move (shared path)

In `useChessGameController.ts:applyPlayerMove`, **before** the blunder-review capture block (after line 152), clear any existing resolved overlay:

```typescript
if (resolvedReview !== null) {
  setResolvedReview(null);
}
```

This runs only for successful moves (illegal moves exit at line 143/147). Both click-to-move and drag/drop use this path.

### Normal game-end: `handleGameEnd` (`useChessGameLifecycle.ts:150`)

Add `setResolvedReview(null)` after `setIsGameActive(false)`. This covers checkmate, stalemate, draw, and any terminal review move. Without this, a review move that ends the game would leave `resolvedReview` stuck in `pending` forever since `AnalysisEffects` bails out when `!isGameActive`.

### Resign: `handleResign` (`useChessGameLifecycle.ts:335`)

Add `setResolvedReview(null)` after `setIsGameActive(false)`.

### Revert: `executeRevert` (`useChessGameLifecycle.ts:186-188`)

Add `setResolvedReview(null)` alongside existing `setBlunderReviewId(null)`.

### New game: `handleNewGame` (`useChessGameLifecycle.ts:262-263`)

