### Clarification: searchmoves guard

The engine evaluation call (step 7) must check `searchmoves?.length > 0`, not just truthiness. An empty array is truthy in JS, and `searchmoves` will be `[]` when the cached best move is the only legal move (forced-move positions) or near-terminal positions. Passing an empty `searchmoves` to Stockfish with `multipv: 2` would produce no results.

Guard:
```ts
if (cachedBest && searchmoves && searchmoves.length > 0) {
  evaluatePosition(displayedFen, { depth: 21, multipv: 2, searchmoves });
} else {
  evaluatePosition(displayedFen, { depth: 21, multipv: 3 });
}
```

When there's only one legal move (the cached best), the fallback to multipv:3 is fine — Stockfish will return quickly since there's nothing to search.

